## Specs-D6 Spec Tag Display & Sidebar Filtering
**Status:** implemented
**Module:** `frontend/src/views/SpecsView.vue`
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** Specs-G7, Specs-D1

### Tag Data Model

Tags are stored as `Vec<String>` on `SpecItem` (backend) / `string[]` (frontend). Format: `kind:value` (e.g., `stack:frontend`, `module:specs`).

```typescript
function parseTag(tag: string): { type: string; value: string; full: string } {
  const idx = tag.indexOf(':')
  if (idx > 0) {
    return { type: tag.slice(0, idx), value: tag.slice(idx + 1), full: tag }
  }
  return { type: 'other', value: tag, full: tag }
}
```

### Tag Display in Rows

- **Shortened**: `stack:frontend` renders as `frontend`
- **Color-coded**: `stack:*` = blue (`hsl(200)`), `module:*` = purple (`hsl(280)`)
- **Tooltip**: hover shows full tag text
- **Limit**: max 2 tags shown inline; `+N` overflow indicator
- Applied to: `GoalsTable`, `SpecItemRow` (Architecture, Designs, Plans, Tests, Reviews, Reports)

### Module Accordion Navigation

The sidebar is organized as a module accordion tree:

```
ŌöīŌöĆ Sidebar ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ
Ōöé ­¤ō¢ Overview                            Ōöé
Ōöé ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  Ōöé
Ōöé Ō¢╝ agent-config                         Ōöé
Ōöé   ­¤ōä Outline                           Ōöé
Ōöé   ­¤Ä» Goals (1)                         Ōöé
Ōöé   ­¤ÅŚ’ĖÅ Architecture (1)                  Ōöé
Ōöé   ...                                  Ōöé
Ōöé Ō¢╝ api-sources                          Ōöé
Ōöé   ­¤ōä Outline                           Ōöé
Ōöé   ...                                  Ōöé
Ōöé ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  Ōöé
Ōöé <details open> Stack                   Ōöé
Ōöé   [All] [backend] [frontend] [both]    Ōöé
Ōöé </details>                             Ōöé
ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś
```

- **Overview**: flat top-level item; shown by default when Specs view opens
- **Module drawers**: one `<details>` per module, derived from item ID prefixes (e.g. `AgentConfig-G1` ŌåÆ `agent-config`)
- **Outline**: first item under each module; loads the module's `module.ad` via `GET /module/{module}/outline`
- **Type items**: the 7 spec categories (Goals, Architecture, Designs, Plans, Tests, Reviews, Reports) with item counts

### Filter Logic

Module filtering is implicit: clicking a type under a module shows only items whose ID prefix matches that module. Stack filtering uses tag pills with AND logic:

```typescript
const filteredItems = computed(() => {
  let items = section.items
  if (activeModule.value) {
    items = items.filter(item => idToModule(item.id) === activeModule.value)
  }
  if (selectedStacks.value.length > 0) {
    items = items.filter(item =>
      selectedStacks.value.some(s => item.tags?.includes(`stack:${s}`))
    )
  }
  return items
})
```

- **Module filter**: derived from `idToModule(item.id)`, not tags; `module:` tags are redundant and have been removed
- **Stack filter**: item must match at least one selected stack
- **Empty selection**: counts as "match all" for that filter type
- Tag pills toggle on click; active state styled with primary color

