```

- **Left**: breadcrumb (`ProjectName / ModuleName / SectionTitle`)
- **Center-right**: search input (filters module names and type titles)
- **Right**: action buttons (Drift Check, Rebuild Links)

#### 4. Backend APIs

```
GET /api/forge/specs/{project}/overview
ŌåÆ { content: string, exists: boolean }

GET /api/forge/specs/{project}/module/{module}/outline
ŌåÆ { content: string, exists: boolean }
```

Both endpoints read `.ad` files from the project specs directory:
- `overview.ad` ŌåÆ `{project_dir}/overview.ad`
- `module.ad` ŌåÆ `{project_dir}/{module}/module.ad`

#### 5. State Model

Three mutually exclusive view states:

| State | `showOverview` | `activeModuleOutline` | `activeModule` | `activeSection` |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Project Overview** | `true` | `null` | `""` | `""` |
| **Module Outline** | `false` | `"relay"` | `"relay"` | `""` |
| **Module Section** | `false` | `null` | `"relay"` | `"goals"` |

#### 6. Default View Behavior

On first load (`watch(moduleTree, { immediate: true })`), if no module or overview is active, the view defaults to **Project Overview** (`showOverview = true`). This ensures new users see the high-level system description before diving into individual modules.

### Requirements

- `module:` tags are deprecated and no longer serialized; module membership is derived from ID prefix only
- `module.ad` files are static documents; they are NOT loaded into `SpecsDocument` sections and are NOT overwritten by `save_module_format`
- The module accordion tree is rebuilt dynamically from `document.sections` whenever specs are loaded or saved
